 (spatial vision, complex connections), C (understands tech, attention), D (problem solving, concentration), B (weather, computer), A also.\n\nCalmness/judgment under pressure: C (keeps calm in crisis, quick correct decisions), D (responds adequately to unexpected), B (handles stress well), A (anticipates dangerous situations), but no explicit.\n\nDecision-making: C (quick correct decisions), A (anticipates dangerous), D (problem solving), B (weather assessment).\n\nTeamwork/communication: C (positive atmosphere, concern for others), A (leadership), B (communication issues), D (weak leadership, arrogance), A also leadership.\n\nProfessional development: C not willing to further education (negative), D weak leadership, B good computer skills, A maybe unorganized.\n\nOverall, C seems strong: reliability, calm, quick decisions, crew atmosphere, concern for others, technical understanding, attention, but has communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education. Communication difficulty could affect crew coordination, but positive atmosphere may offset. Egocentric may affect teamwork. Not willing to further education may affect long-term development.\n\nD: strong problem solving, concentration, responsibility, but weak leadership, arrogance, hot temper, know-it-all. Leadership is important for long-distance crew coordination. Weak leadership is a serious drawback.\n\nB: handles stress, conscientious, good weather assessment, computer skills, but communication tone issues, uncooperative, grumpy. Could affect crew.\n\nA: leadership, anticipates danger, spatial vision, but unorganized, poor at criticism, no explicit stress handling.\n\nThus C appears best despite communication issues. However need to consider that communication difficulty could be critical for long-distance flights where crew coordination is vital. But C also creates positive atmosphere and concern for others, which may mitigate. Also 100% reliability is huge.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate C.\n\nUncertainties: communication difficulty and egocentric attitude could impair crew cooperation; also unwillingness to further education may affect long-term suitability. If we had more info on how severe communication issues are, could change.\n\nThus vote C.\n\nNow produce output."}
