nication issues, because reliability and stress handling are critical for safety. Teamwork can be trained; communication tone can be addressed. A's leadership is good but without reliability it's risky. C's lack of reliability is a bigger issue. D's temperament is also risky.\n\nThus I will provisionally favor Candidate B.\n\nUncertainties: severity of B's nasty remarks and wrong tone; impact of weak memory for numbers on navigation; whether A's leadership could compensate for lack of explicit reliability; whether C's communication difficulty could be mitigated.\n\nWhat would change vote: evidence that B's communication issues lead to crew conflict or safety incidents; evidence of strong reliability for A or C; evidence that A's leadership and technical skills outweigh reliability concerns; evidence that D's temperament is manageable and his responsibility strong.\n\nNow produce public message."}
